HEADWORD: Arenicolite
<hw>Ar`e*nic"o*lite</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>arena</ets> sand + <ets>colere</ets> to cherish or live.]</ety>
<fld>(Paleon.)</fld> <def>An ancient wormhole in sand, preserved in the
rocks.</def> <rj><au>Dana.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>arenicolous</ent>⟦br⟧
